01/11/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- A former Bosnian Serb army member, Radmilo Vukovic, pleaded not guilty to charges of war crimes, during his appearance before the BiH Court on Tuesday (October 31st).
Vukovic is accused of the rape and torture of a Bosniak woman in the Foca region in June 1992.
Also Tuesday, the Sarajevo Cantonal Prosecution filed an indictment against retired Bosnian Serb policeman Borislav Berjan, accusing him of war crimes against non-Serb civilians in the Ilidza municipality.
The crimes allegedly were committed from 1992-1993.
(RTRS, PBS BiH - 31/10/06)
